				<p class='text_block' style="padding-bottom: 0px;">Can machines sense without sensors? Can they "see" without cameras, in the dark, and through the walls? My research is driven by the vision of shaping "<strong>Wireless AI Perception</strong>" to advance machine intelligence beyond vision and language. We focus on pioneering sensing AI technologies that <strong>transform "Homecare" to "Home Cares" and bring healthcare from "Benchside" to "Bedside"</strong>. The field of wireless sensing has experienced tremendous growth in the past 15 years, and I'm fortunate to have my research in this area translated into award-winning products that are deployed in millions of devices worldwide. Currently, my lab is dedicated to designing cutting-edge sensing solutions as well as building commercialized applications for a smarter, more connected life. Our current research interests include:
				<ul style="list-style-type: disc">
				<li><strong>Sensing AI for Homecare, Healthcare, Eldercare</strong></li>
				<li><strong>Localization for Mobiles, Robots, Drones</strong></li>
				<li><strong>AI for Healthcare</strong></li>
				<li><strong>Automotive In-Cabin Sensing</strong></li>
				</ul>
			</p>
